# ==============================================================================
# Privacy belt-and-braces: never commit a user's uploaded genome or CGM data,
# even if someone accidentally drags a file into the repo. The /upload flow
# never writes to disk, but if a file appears in the working tree it stays
# untracked.
# ==============================================================================
*.txt
*.tsv
*.csv
*.pdf
genome*
cgm*
ottai*
23andme*
ancestry*
# Allow project-relevant text files explicitly:
!README.md
!**/requirements.txt
!frontend/**/*.tsx
!frontend/**/*.ts
!backend/**/*.py
# Project data CSVs (Shanghai cohort) live in backend/data/ and are public.
!backend/data/*.csv
!backend/data/*.json
